6:
That's the only reason I've kept
fighting this long.
17:
Ah, you're in luck, young man! The
one and only Barrek is just about to
finish off his opponent!
22:
Was that all you could muster?
Disappointing.
24: Damn it... I couldn't even touch him.
27:
Someone get this failure some
medical attention.
30:
Did you see that?! Ahaha! That's the
former champ for ya!
36:
Yeah... He's got one hell of a right
hook.
40:
But what else did you expect from
Barrek? He's king of the mountain
when it comes to the pro fighting
world!
42:
They say that he relaxes at a local
tavern after his matches, but I'm too
nervous to go check it out myself...
44:
Ah! But you young bucks could do it
for me! Please, will you go and get
his autograph for this old coot?
50:
Excuse me, you're Barrek, aren't you?
Could we have your autograph?
54: Hm? Sure, kid. But on one condition.
56:
Don't go telling people where you
found me.
58:
I've had my fill of sorry-ass fighters
challenging me out of nowhere.
62: I think I like this guy.
65:
You were pretty awesome out there.
How'd you get that strong, anyway?
69:
Simple. I kept on fighting. There's no
shortcuts or anything.
71:
But it helps to have higher stakes
when it comes to training.
74:
Unlike that chump from before, it
looks like you already know that.
Wanna fight?
78:
Oh, man! I really wish we could, but
look at the time...
81: Hmph. Just say you're not up to it.
85:
How about you, Hellcat of the
Dunes? You wanna rumble?
90:
Wait, how do you know that name?
Could you be...
97:
Would explain a lot. Fighting on top
of sand hones your body. Besides,
I've fought someone who moves just
like him...
99: Though that man was a hired killer...
103:
You've found me out. These fists
WERE tempered for assassination.
105:
But YOUR fists made me the man I
am today. Our fight brought me
here, to the Endless Blue, and led me
to my title in the ring.
108:
Huh? So when did you drift to this
world?
113:
It's a long story. If we're not going to
duel, then let's at least have a seat
together. I want to hear YOUR story
first.
117:
I see. So you're on a world-flipping
adventure.
119:
Sounds fun. I bet I could find
incredible opponents if I went
off-world.
122:
Aheh... That's not really the point of
our journey...
125:
No life is complete without a worthy
rival. I'm jealous you guys get to
actually seek one out.
130: You could come with, you know.
140: Wait, don't I get a say?!
144:
He's eager to fight. He could help us
get rid of all those unsavory sorts
who keep pesterin' us.
148:
If you've got enemies, I've got
solutions. Two of 'em, in fact.
152:
Haven't you guys ever tried to settle
your problems through talking first?!
154:
But fine... I know when I'm
outmatched.
163:
Now let's get a move on. I'm itching
for some trouble.
